    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{t}{t+1}-\frac{5t+6}{t^{2}+t}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{t-6}{t}, t\ne -1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{t}{t+1}-\frac{5t+6}{t^{2}+t}} 
      \amp = {\frac{t}{t+1}}-\frac{{5t+6}}{t(t+1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{t \cdot t}{({t+1}) \cdot t}-\frac{{5t+6}}{t(t+1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{t^{2}}{t(t+1)}-\frac{{5t+6}}{t(t+1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{t^{2}-({5t+6})}{t(t+1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{t^{2}-5t-6}}{t(t+1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{(t+1)(t - 6)}{t(t+1)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t-6}{t}, t\ne -1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{t+1}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {-1}</m>.</p>
</solution>
